FAQs
What are the benefits of studying medicine in Europe?
Studying medicine in Europe offers high academic standards, affordable tuition fees, diverse cultural experiences, shorter duration of study, and practical training opportunities.

How can Qadri-International help me study medicine abroad?
Qadri-International provides comprehensive guidance, application assistance, visa support, financial planning, and pre-departure and post-arrival support to ensure a smooth and successful study abroad experience.

Are there English-taught medical programs in Europe?
Yes, many European universities offer medical programs taught in English, making it accessible for international students.

What are the costs associated with studying medicine in Europe?
The costs include tuition fees, which range from €2,000 to €20,000 per year, and living expenses, which range from €600 to €1,200 per month. Scholarships and financial aid are available to help reduce these costs.

How do I apply to study medicine in Europe?
The application process generally involves submitting an online application form, academic transcripts, a personal statement, letters of recommendation, and proof of language proficiency. Qadri-International can assist with each step of the application process.
